            <!-- Mac Features Section -->
            <div class="mb-12">
                <h2 class="font-heading font-bold text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-8 text-center">
                    Essential Mac Features
                </h2>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                    <div class="card-hover">
                        <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Seamless Integration</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                            Apple headphones offer instant pairing, automatic switching between devices, and deep integration with macOS features like Siri and Find My.
                        </p>
                    <div class="card-hover">
                        <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">High-Quality Audio Codecs</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                            Mac supports advanced audio codecs like AAC and ALAC, ensuring high-quality audio streaming when paired with compatible headphones.
                        </p>
                    <div class="card-hover">
                        <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Multi-Device Support</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                            Many headphones can connect to multiple devices simultaneously, allowing seamless switching between your Mac, iPhone, and iPad.
                        </p>
                    <div class="card-hover">
                        <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">macOS Audio Features</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                            Take advantage of macOS features like spatial audio, headphone accommodations, and system-wide audio controls for the best experience.
                        </p>
            <!-- FAQ Section -->
            <div class="mb-12">
                <h2 class="font-heading font-bold text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-8 text-center">
                    Frequently Asked Questions
                </h2>
                <div class="space-y-6">
                    <div class="card-hover">
                        <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Do I need Apple headphones for Mac?</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                            While Apple headphones offer the best integration, most Bluetooth headphones work well with Mac. The key is finding headphones with good macOS compatibility.
                        </p>
                    <div class="card-hover">
                        <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">What audio codecs does Mac support?</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                            Mac supports AAC, ALAC, and SBC codecs. AAC provides the best quality for most users, while ALAC offers lossless audio for audiophiles.
                        </p>
                    <div class="card-hover">
                        <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Can I use wired headphones with Mac?</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                            Yes, Mac computers have headphone jacks that support both 3.5mm and USB-C connections. Wired headphones often provide the best audio quality.
                        </p>
